<doc id="102420" wikidata="Q964199" url="?curid=102420" title="Gyaltsab Je">
<text>Gyaltsab Je () (1364 – 1432) or more elaborately, Gyaltsab Dharma Rinchen was born in the Tsang province of central Tibet. He was a famous student of Je Tsongkhapa, and actually became the first Ganden Tripa (throne holder) of the Gelug tradition after Je Tsongkhapa&#x27;s death. He also studied with Rendawa Zhonnu Lodro (red mda&#x27; ba gzhon nu blo gros, 1349–1412).

Gyaltsab Je was a prolific writer; one of his most famous texts is a commentary of Shantideva&#x27;s &quot;A Guide to the Bodhisattva&#x27;s Way Of Life&quot;. Lodrö Tenpa, the seventh Ganden Tripa, was his student.

== References ==
